Citation.sTitle: The liquid-liquid coexistence curves of {x dimethyl adipate + (1 - x) n-octane} and {x dimethyl adipate + (1 - x) n-nonane} in the critical region
Citation.sAbstract: The liquid-liquid coexistence curves of {dimethyl adipate + n-octane} and {dimethyl adipate + n-nonane} have been determined within about 10 K from the critical temperatures, from which the critical amplitudes and the critical exponents are deduced. The critical exponents corresponding to the coexistence curve beta are consistent with the 3D-Ising values. The experimental results have been analyzed to determine Wegner-correction terms and to discuss the asymmetric behavior of the diameters of the coexistence curves by the complete scaling theory. Molar mass-dependences of the critical amplitude and the critical volume fraction have been shown to be consistent with the theoretical prediction.
